  "analysis": "The implementation compiles and the forward-send bug was patched, but no behavioral verification has been run yet. The most complete proposed verification script is Panel 3's, but it has a fundamental flaw: each pipeline rank creates a separate model with the same seed, but `train_step_pipeline_afab` only updates each rank's local partition. Comparing a rank's full uninitialized/untrained parameter gradients against a full reference model will fail for unowned ranks/parameters. I need a verification script that compares only owned partition gradients and uses identical model state across ranks. I will use a robust script with file-based gradient collection and exact reference comparison for world_size 1 and 2.",
  "plan": "Create `/tmp/test_pp.py` that:
- Spawns gloo processes for world_size 1 and 2.
- Builds identical models on all ranks from a fixed seed and shares state via file or object broadcast.
- Runs `train_step_pipeline_afab` with 2 microbatches.
- Collects only owned parameter gradients (embed on rank 0, assigned decoder layers on all ranks, norm/lm_head on last rank).
- Runs a reference full forward/backward with the same model and microbatch loss scaling.
- Compares loss and gradients numerically.
Then run the script and inspect failures.",
